    <h2>Frequent asked questions</h2>
<b>Who can carry out an adoption?</b>    <br />
Any person, fully capable, over 18 years of age, upon signing the adoption contract.
    <br />
    <br />
    <b>What documents are required for an adoption?</b>    <br />
    ID, and proof of address. It is necessary to present the original ID also on the day of the pet's removal. If renting a house/flat a letter from the owner authorizing the adoption will also be required.
    <br />
    <br />
    <b>Are animals up for adoption neutered?</b>    <br />
    Yes. The animals are neutered, vaccinated according to age, dewormed, microchipped and receive flea and tick control medications, in accordance with current legislation.
